Daily menu of an obese child: no sausage breakfast and dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 are overweight, with overweight affecting 9% of the school population and obesity affecting 5%.
Obese children come mostly from families with unhealthy lifestyles, according to current research.
It again demonstrates the importance of the environment in which one grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference.
At the table, obsessed children eat sausages at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had had chips for dinner the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence."
In families of overweight children there is no habit of practicing sports, which is applicable to most families today, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
A survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and involved almost 900 children of Basic Education from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program “Obesity is not a coincidence”, which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children from 4th to 8th grade have participated in the project.
A proper diet and enough exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of overweight and even obese children.
“Only half of the children surveyed responded that they have five meals a day according to the diet: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet,” one of the survey results says.
No breakfast but sausage for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to discover that in 10% of households they do not eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that families of obese children consume insane chips much more often.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet soda daily (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed play sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make Your Diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal."
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
“The popularity of sweet soda is especially alarming,” the study’s final report warns.
As the main meal, the pasta is taken from the palm and the poultry meat follows it closely.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases a major change in favor of the principles of healthy eating," the study results said.
Attention is drawn, for example, to sweet soda, where many children would start to prefer regular water.
Children would also more often choose poultry and fish for the main meal and restrict consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
