In Need for Speed: The Run, you compete all over America.
Review
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper neglects of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To a certain extent, expectations were met, but that was of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which The Run is added, aroused great expectations already before its release.
It promised that it would give new airs to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result of what is shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being an action genre again without more.
We are also curious to know how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in total counting points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality they cannot even be called errors, but rather it is the incomprehensible reluctance of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphic is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumnal landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, the races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
In the mountains, however, you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of opponents (normal in a classic race), then you try to win time (timed classic duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the midst of all this, the police sometimes appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that nowadays it is no longer a big thing, but you can not say that it is bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action is quite suitable for this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, all in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
From games of this type you can not expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled spins.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no major problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resettings are programmed in such a way that, when you have an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very trustworthy.
Sometimes, even resetting does not help, it only helps to learn the given stage from memory.
A major disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or you arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have an advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always overtake you in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, whatever the price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front, so at first you can make the car dough.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you will surely be disappointed right away.
And it’s a shame, because although the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so that it doesn’t fit boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to pay attention to the gas supplies next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are suitable for urban areas, the American strong cars for straight highways and the exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition main narrative thread also appears a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both the challenges and the stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community features available.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is done.
With the car you get to the metro tunnel (passe), where you start to run in the dark along the tracks (passe).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the subway convoy and is carried in front of you without further ado.
In the newsroom we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or whether the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where there are many participants involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the "each of his father and mother" category, but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for its music.
Need for Speed: The Run is a bit confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly errors, we would have trouble stating that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but be prepared because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of some airport reflectors.
The Carolina University choirs will participate in the concert "Velvet Students".
The joint celebration of International Students’ Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
Twenty choirs from high schools and universities will be presented during the event.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
