Casino forgives Jonás Larrazábal and will go free
After 72 days of roots, the legal representative of the Casino Red granted the pardon to the brother of the mayor of Monterrey of the process that was followed by alleged blackmail
After 72 days in prison, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal will be released after the legal representative of the Casino Red granted him pardon before the Second District Criminal Court, which is following a blackmail process against the brother of the mayor of Monterrey.
After the attack on the Casino Royale, the owner of the Casino Red, Sergio Gil García, made public a series of photographs and videos in which Manuel Jonás allegedly demanded the payment of an economic fee for the city council to allow the clandestine operation of the bookmaker.
Following the public denunciation, the State Prosecutor’s Office opened a criminal case against the brother of the Panista mayor and on 2 September he was arrested and entrenched for 30 days.
After four hours before the Public Prosecutor 3 in Patrimonial Crimes, he was transferred to the House of Arraigo 1, located in the Old Quarter of the capital of the State.
He remained there for the next 49 days after a second arrest warrant was issued after the Public Prosecutor ' s Office dismissed the crimes of bribery and organized crime.
On October 19, he was transferred to Cadereyta prison for allegedly blackmailing the owners of the Casino Red with 1.5 million pesos; however, he remained only a few hours in the medium-security prison as there were death threats against him.
The authorities allowed him to follow the trial held in the municipal cells of San Nicolás de los Garza.
On October 25, an arrest warrant was issued by the secretary of the Second District Criminal Court, Jorge Yánez, who said that after almost two months of investigations, enough evidence was found to determine Jonas’ guilt, such as the collection of 1.5 million pesos from the bookmaker’s representatives in exchange for allowing the operation of the bookmaker.
This Monday, the legal representative of Casino Red, Víctor Aldo García Gómez, went before the judge José Luis Pecina to request the pardon for the brother of the regal mayor; so that in the next hours he could recover his freedom.
During the legal process, the agent of the Public Prosecutor attached to the Court, Ramiro Arias, questioned García Gómez if the damage had been repaired and which of the partners of the bookmaker was the one who granted the pardon, although the lawyer tried to reserve the name.
On the basis of file 197/2011, the legal pardon is granted to Jonás Larrazábal and thereafter no claim can be made regarding the process that followed him; in addition, he will not be required to make reparation for damages or punishment.
After the hearing to the legal representative of the bookmaker, around 15:50 the immediate release of Larrazabal Bretón was ordered.
The secretary of the Court, Jorge Yánez, moved to the prison of the municipality of San Nicolás de los Garza to notify Jonás that he has been legally pardoned and his file will be archived.
It will also notify you of the immediate release order issued by the judge.
Secretary Dionisio Pérez Jácome gives details of the plane crash where the Secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake, and seven other people lost their lives
The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results of the accident in which the Secretary of the Interior, Francisco Blake Mora, and seven other people died indicate that the helicopter impacted directly on the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to attempt a forced landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Pérez Jácome, secretary of Communications and Transport, mentioned that before taking off the aircraft, the pilot found that the weather conditions were adequate to fly.
"The elements that appear to indicate that the unit had several contacts with the ground, the blades had contact with trees 25 meters away where the unit lost the fuselage."
It also reported that the unit was designed for 19 people, so it had the necessary requirements to transport personnel.
In addition, he said that in the investigations made in the area of the impact there is no report of the appearance of pieces on the ground.
“A search reported that there are no parts or components of the craft elsewhere, the impact was presented structurally.
“The design of the helicopter was for 19 passengers, it had adequate requirements to transport the passengers.
The terrain has a slope of seven degrees at 30 degrees of inclination.
At the moment, the secretary said that it is a priority to have the results as soon as possible; however, the investigation can last several months, it could even reach a year.
For his part, Gilberto López Meyer, director general of Airports and Auxiliary Services, assured that at the time of the impact, the helicopter of the Presidential Staff operated at cruising speed and that this happened on an ascending soft terrain.
"This information strengthens the hypothesis of a normal cruise operation at the time of impact," he said.
In the press conference, the head of the SCT, Pérez Jácome, listed six relevant elements in the investigation:
Visual flight:
According to aeronautical regulations the flight was made under visual flight rules, this implies that the crew must have visibility during the flight and on the ground.
Weather conditions:
Reports in the AICM located suitable conditions for takeoff, as the aircraft advanced towards the area bordering between the DF and the State of Mexico there were layers of cloudiness at low altitude.
Selected routes:
It is likely that due to the cloudy conditions the crew has sought an area of lower elevation and greater visibility towards the Cuernavaca valley.
Location of impact.
The impact coordinates and the last radar record of the aircraft coincide, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or disturbance in the flight path.
Dispersion of aircraft debris in a reduced area:
The information available so far allows us to assume that the impact occurred in a straight and sideways trajectory.
The pattern of dispersion of debris of the aircraft allows to assume that the helicopter was impacted on the ground in conditions of structural integrity.
No evidence of fire or explosion was detected:
At the site of the accident, no evidence of any kind of explosion or fire is revealed in the remains of the ship.
The latest results of the investigation indicate that he may have had multiple contacts with the ground.
During fieldwork, parts of the aircraft have been found at an elevation of 9,200 feet above mid-sea level, the terrain presents a slope ranging from seven degrees to 30 degrees of inclination.
The photographs show the sequence in which it was predictably disarticulated along that path.
The information provides elements that appear to indicate that the helicopter may have had multiple impacts on the ground.
After a thorough search in a wider area than the cordoned off site around the crash, no scattered parts of the aircraft have been found, reinforcing the presumption that the impact occurred under structural integrity conditions.
MSS Announces Protocol to Find Obesity Gene
Social Security Leads Research to Discover Obesity Gene in Children and Youth; Supported by IPN Specialists
The Mexican Institute of Social Security (IMSS) announced that it is leading research to discover the gene of obesity in children and young people, called the protocol 'Genetics of childhood and adolescence obesity', which will allow us to have markers associated with overweight.
In a statement, the head of the Medical Research Unit in Biochemistry of the Hospital of Specialties of the National Medical Center Siglo XXI, Miguel Cruz López, explained that a multidisciplinary team of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers was integrated.
This team is supported by specialists and graduate students from the National Institute of Public Health (INSP) and the Center for Research and Advanced Studies (Cinvestav) of the National Polytechnic Institute (IPN).
In the research the population is invited to participate, whether or not they are entitled, to go to the participating sports units of the IMSS in the Valley of Mexico, where tests are carried out for minors, every Saturday from 8:00 a.m.
He stressed that the protocol began at the Cuauhtémoc Sports Unit (State of Mexico West) and that since October 8, the activity is carried out at the Nezahualcóyolt Sports Unit (State of Mexico East).
Once the goal of bringing together 500 or 600 minors is met, the study will continue in the Unidad Deportiva Independencia (south of the Federal District) and finally in the Unidad Deportiva Morelos (north of the Federal District).
He explained that the purpose of this research is to know the components and the importance of genetics with respect to the development of obesity and to identify in Mexican children and young people risk factors to prevent the appearance of chronic degenerative diseases.
As World Diabetes Day is celebrated on November 14, the goal is to bring together 3,000 children and young people between the ages of six and 14, with the consent and supervision of their parents, for the application of specific questionnaires on diet.
They will also be asked about physical activity and hereditary family history of diseases, in order to avoid risk factors that trigger conditions such as diabetes or kidney failure.
All participants are given anthropometric measurements (weight, height, waist circumference), blood pressure measurements, determination of glucose, triglycerides, cholesterol and insulin levels, and genetics (we seek to identify genes that are associated with childhood obesity).
Cruz Lopez noted that this research is due to the concern of health professionals about the alarming weight gain in minors.
"The 1999 and 2006 health surveys indicated that in just six years there was an increase, in the case of boys, of 77 percent in obesity, and in the case of girls of 47 percent; in terms of overweight, a dramatic rise was also observed," said the IMSS specialist.
He said the justification for the search for the markers is based on the fact that the country’s population differs from others in its genetic history.
He reported that on average, the Mexican has 65 percent American Indian, 30 percent European and five percent African heritage and this condition is reflected in the genes that are associated with diabetes and overweight.
He explained that in general, the genetics of obesity translates into the inability to burn the excess energy that we consume (calories) and that is stored in the form of fat.
The researcher explained that the direct benefit for the participants is the comprehensive evaluation of the children, which allows to detect if they are overweight or obese.
Even, he said, the presence of dark-colored folds (acanthosis) in the neck and forearm, indicating the likelihood of metabolic disturbances and even prediabetes.
The information is handled confidentially, doctors give it in writing to parents, who are explained each of the measurements and lifestyle changes they must make to prevent disease.
Cruz Lopez explained that there are three main components that cause overweight, obesity and other chronic conditions: sedentary lifestyle, which is the lack of daily physical activity, sitting most of the day in front of the TV and using means of transport instead of walking short distances.
