This was the work of the caleño who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lophoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lophoscopist of the Cali CTI went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the FARC chief: "Alfonso Cano", through the collation of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopists who work in the sectional of the CTI, that week it was the turn of "availability" to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to stay for more than five days in the jungle to get to the place where the corpses that had to be identified were.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopy, which is the study of the friction skin, that is, of the palms of the hands and of the feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothing for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to carry the decadactile card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigation team at the site where the body was found, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the FARC’s chief.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typewriter from the Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know about our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, without margin of error, that can become key in the resolution of crimes.
Aside from identifying corpses, lophoscopists support investigations into crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identities of those captured.
When caught, many criminals present fake banknotes or have no papers.
We took their fingerprints and looked them up in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to take a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Fingerprints can also dismiss or reaffirm suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with liquor bottles around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a relative could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that it was the killer, it does place him at the crime scene.
A CTI typist explained that in the objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registrar.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," the CTI expert said.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI television show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes footprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective collation is performed.
