Other experts in the field of health law have already expressed their reservations about the conclusions of the report of the Royal Society of Canada experts.
Pierre Deschamps, a specialist in health law, has called the stance of the experts who signed the report "extreme", among other things because the practice of euthanasia is not limited to terminally ill patients.
